        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory-wiki): accept apply op aliases",
        "body": "Summary\n- Fixes #90303.\n- Accept CLI-style `wiki_apply` op aliases (`synthesis`, `metadata`) alongside the internal names (`create_synthesis`, `update_metadata`).\n- Normalize aliases before mutation validation so `synthesis` follows the synthesis path and `metadata` follows the metadata path.\n- Add focused regression tests for both aliases.\n- Review update: widen the raw input op type before alias comparison so strict extension typecheck accepts the comparisons while the normalizer still returns internal ops only.\n\nBehavior Proof\n\nBefore this patch, the `wiki_apply` schema only accepted `create_synthesis` and `update_metadata`, so an agent call such as `{\"op\":\"synthesis\",\"title\":\"Test Synthesis\",\"body\":\"Some body text\",\"sourceIds\":[\"sources/example.md\"]}` failed schema validation with `ValidationError: op must be equal to constant`.\n\nAfter this patch, I exercised the real `wiki_apply` tool implementation from this branch against a temporary memory-wiki vault. The proof script called the actual tool with `op: \"synthesis\"` and then `op: \"metadata\"`; the output shows both aliases accepted and normalized to the internal operations:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"rootDir\": \"/var/folders/zt/6txd70rn1wn9x37_3hkv_ft80000gn/T/openclaw-wiki-alias-proof-VCVTp2\",\n  \"synthesisText\": \"Updated syntheses/alias-proof.md via create_synthesis. Refreshed 4 index files.\",\n  \"synthesisOperation\": \"create_synthesis\",\n  \"synthesisPagePath\": \"syntheses/alias-proof.md\",\n  \"metadataText\": \"Updated syntheses/alias-proof.md via update_metadata. Refreshed 1 index file.\",\n  \"metadataOperation\": \"update_metadata\",\n  \"metadataPagePath\": \"syntheses/alias-proof.md\"\n}\n```\n\nVerification\n- `pnpm test extensions/memory-wiki/src/apply.test.ts`\n  - `Test Files  1 passed (1)`\n  - `Tests  6 passed (6)`\n- `pnpm lint --threads=8`\n  - `oxlint:core` finished\n  - `oxlint:extensions` finished\n  - `oxlint:scripts` finished\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions`\n  - passed\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions:test`\n  - passed\n- `pnpm exec tsx /private/tmp/openclaw-wiki-apply-alias-proof.ts`\n  - produced the real tool output shown above\n\nPlatform Tested\n- macOS arm64, pnpm v11.2.2\n\nLimitations\n- The real behavior proof uses a temporary local memory-wiki vault rather than a long-lived user vault. It exercises the actual `wiki_apply` tool implementation and filesystem-backed mutation path from this branch.",
